Yes 👍 — this step is important, and you’re asking at the right time.


---

🏆 Short Answer

👉 YES — delete old configs before applying new ones

But do it carefully (not blindly everything) 👇


---

🚀 EXACT SAFE STEPS

✅ Step 1: Delete old IDMS

oc delete imagedigestmirrorset --all


---

✅ Step 2: Delete old ITMS

oc delete imagetagmirrorset --all


---

✅ Step 3: Delete old CatalogSource

oc delete catalogsource --all -n openshift-marketplace


---

⚠️ Step 4: Signature ConfigMap (IMPORTANT)

👉 Check first:

oc get configmap -n openshift-config-managed | grep signature

If old exists → delete:

oc delete configmap -n openshift-config-managed -l release.openshift.io/verification-signatures


---

❌ Step 5: DO NOT delete these

👉 Don’t touch:

Nodes ❌

Operators ❌

Namespaces ❌

ClusterVersion ❌



---

🧠 Why deletion is required

If you don’t delete:

❌ Old mirror paths remain
❌ Cluster pulls wrong images
❌ Upgrade fails or behaves weird


---

🏁 After deletion → immediately apply new

oc apply -f idms-oc-mirror.yaml
oc apply -f itms-oc-mirror.yaml
oc apply -f cs-redhat-operator-index-v4-20.yaml
oc apply -f signature-configmap.yaml

(Optional)

oc apply -f updateService.yaml


---

⚠️ Important Timing

👉 Do this ONLY when:

Cluster is stable ✅

No upgrade running ❗



---

🔍 Verify after applying

oc get imagedigestmirrorset
oc get imagetagmirrorset
oc get catalogsource -n openshift-marketplace


---

💡 Pro Tip

👉 After applying, wait 2–3 minutes before upgrade
(so cluster picks new mirror config)


---

👍 Final Answer

👉 ✔ Yes, delete old configs
👉 ✔ Then apply new ones immediately


